'''Ptolemy''' was a famous [[Wizardkind|wizard]] who had been featured on a [[Chocolate Frog Card]] since some point by [[1989]].<ref name="PS6"/><ref name="HM2SC">{{HM|2|Scaredy-Cats}}</ref> 

==History==
By [[1 September]] [[1991]], his Chocolate Frog Card was one of two that [[Ronald Weasley|Ron Weasley]] had yet to collect (the other being [[Cornelius Agrippa]]).<ref name="PS6">{{PS|B|6}}</ref>

==Etymology==
The name "Ptolemy" comes from the Greek name Πτολεμαιος (Ptolemaios), derived from Greek πολεμηιος (polemeios) meaning "aggressive" or "warlike".{{Fact}}

==Behind the scenes==
*There are several historical figures who bore the name Ptolemy, the most famous being {{W|Claudius Ptolemaeus}} (c. 90 AD – c. 168 AD), a mathematician, [[Astronomy (class)|astronomer]], geographer, and astrologer who lived in [[Egypt]] while it was under Roman rule. Another famous historic figure was {{W|Ptolemy I Soter|Ptolemy I}}, who was one of {{W|Alexander the Great}}'s generals. He was the first Pharaoh of the {{W|Ptolemaic dynasty}}.
*Despite being mentioned in the first novel, Ptolemy's [[Chocolate Frog Card]] doesn't appear in any of the {{HPgames}}. [[Rowan Khanna]] mentions obtaining his card in {{HM}}, however.<ref name="HM2SC"/>

